"{\"uid\": \"express.co.uk-showbiz-tv-radio-1935443-Tom-Cruise-Paris-Olympics-stunt-producer-Ben-Winston\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"  Mission ImpossibleactorTom Cruisedelivered a stunt to remember at theOlympicsclosing ceremony - but now his creative director and executive producer Ben Winston has admitted that it was a \\\"nightmare\\\" negotiating all the logistics that went along with it.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 256, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 151, \"end\": 162, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ben_Winston\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ben Winston\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ben_Winston\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ben_Winston\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Tom had insisted on being hands-on and jumping off the roof himself, rather than leaving it to a professional stunt double - so it was high energy from everyone involved.\", \"from\": 258, \"to\": 428, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"[When I initially pitched the stunt to Tom], I told him, it was a man in a balaclava who jumped from the roof of the stadium,\\\" he recalled.\", \"from\": 430, \"to\": 570, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Tom's feedback was, 'I love the idea, only we are not doing a stuntman in a balaclava.\", \"from\": 571, \"to\": 658, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I am going to be the one who jumps off the roof, and I am going to be the one who drives through Paris.'\\\"\", \"from\": 659, \"to\": 764, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 756, \"end\": 761, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999413376, \"rank\": 5.874639019673201e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He continued toThe Hollywood Reporter: \\\"You forget what a nightmare it was.\", \"from\": 766, \"to\": 841, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 785, \"end\": 794, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999174388029, \"rank\": 8.256106269458733e-08, \"text\": \"Hollywood\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I feel like live television might be that.\", \"from\": 842, \"to\": 884, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You forget how much you go through.\\\"\", \"from\": 885, \"to\": 921, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite the strife, there is no doubt that Ben enjoys working with Tom - not least because they have achieved stunts together before.\", \"from\": 923, \"to\": 1056, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"His production company, which also worked on The Grammys and launched hit TV showThe Kardashians, famously sent James Corden into the air in a vintage plane, piloted by none other than Tom.\", \"from\": 1057, \"to\": 1246, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1106, \"end\": 1113, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grammy_Awards\", \"score\": 0.9999999187975879, \"rank\": 4.515645621101353e-08, \"text\": \"Grammys\", \"types\": [\"Q618779\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grammy_Awards\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grammy_Awards\"}, {\"begin\": 1169, \"end\": 1181, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Corden\", \"score\": 0.9999999243800659, \"rank\": 7.561973998968325e-08, \"text\": \"James Corden\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Corden\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Corden\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"READ MORE:Olympics' Los Angeles handover leaves BBC viewers 'fuming' with same complaint    Ben recalled at the time that James had been \\\"really afraid\\\" - and had even sent an email to him begging to get out of it on account of having a wife and three children.\", \"from\": 1248, \"to\": 1509, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1268, \"end\": 1279, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999999979122549, \"rank\": 2.0872891309039324e-09, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}, {\"begin\": 1370, \"end\": 1375, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_VI_and_I\", \"score\": 0.9926943760272448, \"rank\": 0.007099335321261852, \"text\": \"James\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_VI_and_I\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_VI_and_I\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Tom, on the other hand, is a seasoned daredevil who's no stranger to leaping out of aeroplanes and, in one heart-thudding performance, even scaling the Burj Khalifa.\", \"from\": 1511, \"to\": 1676, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Ben has worked with numerous other stars and even produced the London-based show An Audience with Adele to show off the impressive vocals of Britain's best-known songstress.\", \"from\": 1678, \"to\": 1851, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1819, \"end\": 1826, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999943427670538, \"rank\": 2.9774815623271276e-06, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, his music video with Harry Styles took just three hours, whereas he worked with Tom on painstakingly perfecting every last detail for the Olympics for 18 months.\", \"from\": 1853, \"to\": 2023, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1883, \"end\": 1895, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harry_Styles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.8316364314928387e-33, \"text\": \"Harry Styles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harry_Styles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harry_Styles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ben revealed that one of the \\\"only things\\\" that was fake about the shoot was the flag, a fact which enabled them to keep the nature of their project secret from everyone.\", \"from\": 2025, \"to\": 2195, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Do not miss:Tom Cruise causes concern as 'upset' Olympics viewers issue stern warning  Do not miss:Tom Cruise leaves Olympics fans saying same thing as 'huge stunt' sparks frenzy  Do not miss:Olympics closing ceremony start time and TV channel as Paris 2024 comes to close    He held a white flag instead of an Olympics one, so that members of the press assumed he was filming for Mission Impossible - not the Olympics.\", \"from\": 2197, \"to\": 2616, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2209, \"end\": 2219, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tom Cruise\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\"}, {\"begin\": 2296, \"end\": 2306, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tom Cruise\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Fans were suitably surprised when they caught sight of him whisking away the flag from the French capital all the way toHollywood.\", \"from\": 2618, \"to\": 2748, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2709, \"end\": 2715, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9920428577614172, \"rank\": 0.007429299525491715, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Express.co.uk previously told of the \\\"frenzy\\\" his stunt had sparked- althoughsome disappointed fans who'd heard he would be there initially demanded to know where he was.\", \"from\": 2750, \"to\": 2920, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We use your sign-up to provide content in ways you have consented to and to improve our understanding of you.\", \"from\": 2922, \"to\": 3031, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This may include adverts from us and 3rd parties based on our understanding.\", \"from\": 3032, \"to\": 3108, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You can unsubscribe at any time.\", \"from\": 3109, \"to\": 3141, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Read ourPrivacy Policy  Little did they know how worth the wait his jaw-dropping efforts would prove to be.\", \"from\": 3142, \"to\": 3249, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"SEARCH  CONNECT WITH US  TODAY'S PAPER  See today's front and back pages, download the newspaper, order back issues and use the historic Daily Express newspaper archive.\", \"from\": 3251, \"to\": 3420, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3388, \"end\": 3401, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daily_Express\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.745358113241933e-25, \"text\": \"Daily Express\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daily_Express\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daily_Express\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"EXPRESS.CO.UK  Daily Express uses notifications to keep you updated\", \"from\": 3422, \"to\": 3489, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3437, \"end\": 3450, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daily_Express\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.745358113241933e-25, \"text\": \"Daily Express\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daily_Express\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daily_Express\"}]}]}"